      "content": "i get that but i already have my blood work done and my levels have been super stable for weeks. it feels like i'm just over-medicated at this point since i don't have any symptoms. if the blood work is fine, isn't a lower dose basically just a more natural way to maintain that stability? wouldn't it be better to avoid the higher dose if i'm clearly at a good baseline?",
